Rule: Older age (e.g., 54 or 78) is associated with higher income.
Higher education levels (Doctorate) are associated with higher income.
Marital status of married or separated over divorced is associated with higher income.
Race attribute changing from White to Other can be associated with a higher income.
Gender changing from female to male can be associated with higher income.
Increasing hours worked per week (e.g., from 40 to 50) is associated with higher income.
